Moreover, Napier did not fail to observe‚ that there are certain numbers which neither are to be obtained by the multi- plication of any number whatever into itself‚ nor can be resolved into simple unit by division by any number whatever. Thus„ the number 16 is reduced to 1 by four times dividing by the number 2. This discovers 2 as what Napier called the quadru- partient root of 16„ and 16 as the quadruplicate, or fourth power of 2.
